                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have rescued 15 hostages between the ages of 16 and 30 from a house in Polokwane. Limpopo spokesperson Matimba Maluleke says they have arrested three people in connection with the crime. He says all victims have been taken to a place of safety. "Three suspects in their earlier 30s who were found in the house were arrested. They and expected to appear before the Polokwane Magistrates Court on Thursday the 16th of November 2017."